author: Mary Thurwachter
title: ‘All Clams on Deck’ in Sebastian
text:
Gobble up a few clams and raise a few clams for charity at the Sebastian Clambake Lagoon Festival Nov. 6- 8 at Riverview Park on U.S. 1 in Sebastian.
Bill Cala from Port St Lucie came up with the theme — “All Clams on Deck.” Festival-goers can take home the theme on T-shirts designed by Sebastian artist Lisanne Robinson.
The Sebastian Clambake Lagoon Festival will be Nov. 6, 7 and 8 at Riverview Park on U.S. 1 in Sebastian. Contributed Since the festival began in 2002, the Sebastian Clambake Foundation netted more than $500,000 from the event.
If you go, expect to find nearly 100 vendors, a free kids zone, live entertainment, craft beers, fresh seafood (lots of clams, of course!) and landlubber goodies as well as other refreshments.
For a schedule of the bands and more information, visit www.sebastianclambake.com .
